        = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 16\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 5\n| Title               = In a Stew\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred buys a diner, planning to impress the food critic of the Daily Granite newspaper with the dining experience of a lifetime.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 17\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 6\n| Title               = Fred vs. the Energy Crisis\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred believes that he's solved the energy crisis with his invention of a hot tub heated by wind power called \"The Flintstone Rockuzzi\".\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 18\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 7\n| Title               = Fred's Friend in Need\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred helps an old friend, the once-wealthy Rockwell Granite, who needs to secure a large loan from a local banker.\n| LineColor           = #FF681F\n}}\n|}\n\n==Bedrock Cops==\n[[Fred Flintstone|Fred]] and [[Barney Rubble|Barney]] are part-time police officers assisted by the [[Shmoo]] as a trainee where they work under the direction of Sgt. Boulder. The trio fought crime in the city of [[Bedrock (The Flintstones)|Bedrock]], most of the time chasing after [[The Frankenstones]]' pet monster Rockjaw.\n\n====Season 1 (1980\u201381)====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#FFD700; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#FFD700; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#FFD700\"| Title\n! style=\"background:#FFD700; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = Fred Goes Ape\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney are assigned to guard the Bedrock Zoo, but trouble begins when a gorillasaurus escapes.\n| LineColor           = FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = Off the Beaten Track\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney are assigned to guard the Turbo Rock race car at the Bedrock Grand Prix which is stolen by two escaped convicts.\n| LineColor           = FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 3\n| Title               = A Bad Case of Rockjaw\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred, Barney and Shmoo patrol Bedrock Park where they encounter Rockjaw causing mischief by wrecking trees.\n| LineColor           = FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 4\n| Title               = Follow That Dogasaurus\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|13}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney must save Sgt. Boulder's pet dogosaurus and stop the numerous dogosaurus thefts in Bedrock.\n| LineColor           = FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 5\n| Title               = Mountain Frustration\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|20}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney investigate strange noises and footprints on Mount Bedrock and discover that Rockjaw haunts the mountain.\n| LineColor           = FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 6\n| Title               = Bedlam on the Bedrock Express\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Barney load a fortune in gold onto the Bedrock Express, but they inadvertently stack it on a bank robber's railcar.\n| LineColor           = FFD700\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 7\n| Title               = Hot Air to Spare\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|3}}\n| ShortS