eNumber2      = 7\n| Title               = The Ghastly Gatorsaurus\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Pebbles and Bamm-Bamm rush to save Dino from the clutches of a concrete-eating gatorsaurus.\n| LineColor           = B11030\n}}\n|}\n\n==Captain Caveman==\nThis segment serves as a [[prequel]] to the earlier series ''[[Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels]]'', focusing on Captain Caveman's time in [[Bedrock (The Flintstones)|Bedrock]] before he was frozen in ice. Captain Caveman (under his \"secret identity\" of Chester the office boy), [[Betty Rubble|Betty]] and [[Wilma Flintstone|Wilma]] work for Lou Granite (based on [[Lou Grant]]) at ''The Daily Granite''.<ref name=Daytime>{{cite book |last1=Hyatt |first1=Wesley |title=The Encyclopedia of Daytime Television |date=1997 |publisher=Watson-Guptill Publications |isbn=978-0823083152 |pages=159-160}}</ref> To disguise himself as Chester, Captain Caveman wore a pair of glasses and a tie (similar to the Clark Kent persona used by [[Superman]]). Despite the simplicity of his disguise, he required a coat rack and an elaborate transformation sequence to become Captain Caveman.\n\n====Season 1 (1980\u201381)====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#700070; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#700070; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#700070;| Title\n! style=\"background:#700070; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = Clownfoot\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = The villainous Clownfoot and his strongman henchman Samson join forces to rob the First Bank of Bedrock.\n| LineColor           = 700070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = The Maquerader\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|