mation director [[Tex Avery]]. Two segments aired per episode.\n\n====Season 1 (1980\u201381)====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#0000A0; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#0000A0; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#0000A0;| Title\n! style=\"background:#0000A0; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = Mouse Cleaning\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred buys a new home computer that will hopefully help solve his problems with Cavemouse.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = Quiety Please!\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|22}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino is allowed to stay in the house overnight, providing he remains quiet, but Cavemouse makes it difficult for him.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 3\n| Title               = Camp-Out Mouse\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred takes Dino on a camping trip to get away from Cavemouse, but the pesky Cavemouse follows them.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 4\n| Title               = Piece O'Cake\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|11|29}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred bakes a surprise birthday cake for Barney and assigns Dino to guard it from Cavemouse.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 5\n| Title               = Beach Party\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Dino try to enjoy a fun day at the beach, but the pesky Cavemouse keeps spoiling their fun.\n| LineColor        