sodeNumber2      = 12\n| Title               = Rocko Socko\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|12|27}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred purchases Rocko Socko, a robot programmed to get rid of all pests and freeloaders, to eliminate Cavemouse.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 13\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 13\n| Title               = Aloha Mouse\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred, Wilma and Dino take a cruise to Hawaii and enjoy the voyage until Cavemouse appears.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 14\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 14\n| Title               = Arcade Antics\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino and Cavemouse play on the amusement machines while on night watch at a penny arcade and also encounter a burglar.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 15\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 15\n| Title               = Come Home, Dino\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = Cavemouse removes Dino's license tag from his neck and sends him to the animal shelter, but soon gets a guilty conscience.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 16\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 16\n| Title               = Robin Mouse\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = While Fred and Dino go fishing on Lake Sherwood, Cavemouse meets with rodent hero Robin Mouse.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 17\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 17\n| Title               = A Fool for Pool\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino chases Cavemouse through the pockets of Fred's new pool table, ruining it.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 18\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 18\n| Title               = L'il Orphan Alphie\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Alphie Mouse arrives at the Flintstone house playing the poor orphan who desperately needs something to eat.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 19\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 19\n| Title               = Abra-Ca-Dino\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred demonstrates his new magic kit to Dino but after Fred leaves, Dino uses the magic tricks on Cavemouse.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 20\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 20\n| Title               = The Bedrock 500\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino and Cavemouse compete against each other in the Bedrock 500 automobile race.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 21\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 21\n| Title               = Who is What?\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|31}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred disguises himself in a Dino costume to confuse Cavemouse, but Cavemouse convinces Dino to turn the tables on Fred.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 22\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 22\n| Title               = Pow-Pow the Dyno-Mite\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|1|31}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino is visited by his second cousin Pow-Pow who wants to help him capture Cavemouse.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n|}\n\n====Season 2 (1981\u201382)====\n{| class=wikitable style=\"background:#FFFFFF\"\n|- style=\"color:#FFFFFF\"\n! style=\"background:#0000A0; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|N\u00ba|Number}}\n! style=\"background:#0000A0; width:20px\"| {{Abbr|Ep|Episode}}\n! style=\"background:#0000A0;| Title\n! style=\"background:#0000A0; width:135px\"| Original air date\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 23\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 1\n| Title               = Goofed-Up Golf\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino and Cavemouse chase each other around the golf course while Fred attempts to win a golf contest.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 24\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 2\n| Title               = Sleepy Time Mouse\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|12}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino wants to get a good night's sleep, but the pesky Cavemouse keeps him awake all night.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 25\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 3\n| Title               = S'No Place Like Home\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred takes Dino skiing and, naturally, Cavemouse accompanies them and complicates matters on the ski slope.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 26\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 4\n| Title               = Super-Dupes\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|19}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino and Cavemouse each summon their favorite superheroes to aid them in their endless feud.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 27\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 5\n| Title               = Dinner for Two\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|9|26}}\n| ShortSummary        = Dino frees Cavemouse from a locked box so that the rodent can enjoy a romantic evening with his girlfriend.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 28\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 6\n| Title               = Invasion of the Cheese Snatchers\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1980|9|26}}\n| ShortSummary        = After his spacecraft runs out of fuel, an alien space mouse invades the Flintstone house.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 29\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 7\n| Title               = Handle with Scare\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Cavemouse pretends to be an explosive red robot mouse that escaped from a laboratory to trick Dino and Fred.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 30\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 8\n| Title               = The World's Strongest Mouse\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|3}}\n| ShortSummary        = Cavemouse becomes the strongest mouse in the world with the help of a relaxation technique.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 31\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 9\n| Title               = Bat's All\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = With the help of a tiny lost vampire mouse, Cavemouse outwits Dino and consumes all the food in Fred's kitchen.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 32\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 10\n| Title               = Trick or Treat\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|10}}\n| ShortSummary        = On Halloween, Dino and Cavemouse fight over the candy while trick or treating.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 33\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 11\n| Title               = Do or Diet\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = After Fred locks up his diet food, a robber empties the refrigerator but Cavemouse outwits him and saves Fred's food.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 34\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 12\n| Title               = Mouse for Sale\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|17}}\n| ShortSummary        = Fred and Dino sell Cavemouse to a laboratory, but the plan backfires when they are caught in the lab's electrical current.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 35\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 13\n| Title               = Maltcheese Falcon\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Cavemouse assumes the guise of a gangster, Shnooz, to trick Dino into relinquishing Fred's food.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 36\n| EpisodeNumber2      = 14\n| Title               = Invisible Mouse\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|1981|10|24}}\n| ShortSummary        = Cavemouse gives Fred and Dino a chilling experience when he becomes invisible with Fred's invisibility spray.\n| LineColor           = 0000A0\n}}\n|}\n\n==The Frankenstones==\nThis segment featured the Flintstones' neighbors [[The Frankenstones]]: Frank, his wife Hidea, their kooky daughter Atrocia, and their teenage son Freaky who is friends with fellow teenager [[Pebbles Flintstone]].\n\n===Season 1 (1980\u201381)===\n# Birthday Boy <small>(November 22, 1980)</small> - Freaky's birthday party is disrupted when Frank refuses Pebbles to visit, but Pebbles arrives anyway \u2013 disguised as a witch.\n# Potion Problem <small>(November 29, 1980)</small> - Atrocia creates a hate potion that Frank uses on Pebbles and Freaky to break up their friendship.\n# A Night on the Town <small>(December 6, 1980)</small> - The Flintstones and the Frankenstones have a night on the town that soon turns into a disaster.\n# Out of Their League <small>(December 13, 1980)</small> - When they become coaches of opposing baseball teams, Fred challenges Frank's team to a playoff.\n# Clone for a Day <small>(December 20, 1980)</small> - Atrocia clones a \"nice\" Fred to keep Frank from losing his temper for one full day so he can collect his inheritance.\n# A Stone is Born <small>(December 27, 1980)</small> - Fred appears in a live TV commercial at the same time that Frank repairs the blown fuses at the TV station.\n# A Rocks-Pox on You <small>(January 3, 1981)</small> - Frank contracts the contagious Rocks-Pox disease and the doctor quarantines him along with the Flintstones.\n# The Luck Stops Here <small>(January 10, 1981)</small> - When Fred causes Frank to break a mirror, the Frankenstone family's bad luck is cursed only with good luck.\n# The Monster of Invention <small>(January 17, 1981)</small> - Fred and Frank try to out-invent one another while competing for the grand prize at the Inventor's Fair.\n# Rock and Rolling Frankenstones <small>(January 24, 1981)</small> - Frank becomes a superstar at a rock concert when audience members are enthralled by his smashing hot temper.\n# Sand Doom <small>(January 31, 1981)</small> - By coincidence, the Flintstones and the Frankenstones win a vacation at the same resort.\n\n===Season 2 (1981\u201382)===\n# Pet Peeves <small>(September 12, 1981)</small> - Dino and Rockjaw want to become movie stars when a movie producer holds a contest to discover new animal talent.\n# The Charity Bizarre <small>(September 19, 1981)</small> - The Frankenstones open a carnival to prevent officers Fred and Barney from foreclosing their home.\n# Getting the Business <small>(September 26, 1981)</small> - When Fred and Frank go into the lunch truck business, their recipes gain the attention of the health inspector.\n# Ugly is Only Skin Deep <small>(October 3, 1981)</small> - When Wilma and Hidea are sick with the flu, Fred and Frank take their places in the Bedrock Beauty Contest.\n# Three Days of the Mastodon <small>(October 10, 1981)</small> - Fred and Frank's initiation into the Mastodon Lodge challenge them into playing practical jokes on each other.\n# First Family Fiasco <small>(October 17, 1981)</small> - The Frankenstones and the Flintstones compete for the First Family of Bedrock award.\n# House Wars <small>(October 24, 1981)</small> - When Hidea and Wilma leave to visit a distant relative, Fred and Frank wage a war to make each other move.\n\n==Voice cast==\n* [[Gay Autterson]] as [[Betty Rubble]], Wiggy Rockstone\n* [[Mel Blanc]] as [[Barney Rubble]], [[Captain Caveman and the Teen Angels|Captain Caveman]], [[Dino (The Flintstones)|Dino]]\n* [[Henry Corden]] as [[Fred Flintstone]]\n* [[Ruta Lee]] as [[The Frankenstones|Hidea Frankenstone]]\n* [[Kenneth Mars]] as Lou Granite\n* [[Mitzi McCall]] as Penny Pillar\n* [[Don Messick]] as Schleprock\n* [[Charles Nelson Reilly]] as [[The Frankenstones|Frank Frankenstone]]\n* [[Paul Reubens]] as [[The Frankenstones|Freaky Frankenstone]]\n* [[Zelda Rubinstein]] as [[The Frankenstones|Atrocia Frankenstone]]\n* [[Michael Sheehan (actor)|Michael Sheehan]] as [[Bamm-Bamm Rubble]]\n* [[John Stephenson (actor)|John Stephenson]] as Mr. Slate\n* [[Russi Taylor]] as [[Pebbles Flintstone]], Cavemouse\n* [[Jean Vander Pyl]] as [[Wilma Flintstone]]\n* [[Lennie Weinrib]] as Moonrock Crater, Sgt. Boulder\n* [[Frank Welker]] as [[Shmoo]], [[The Frankenstones|Rockjaw]]\n\n===Additional voices===\n* [[Ren\u00e9 Auberjonois]]\n* [[Joe Baker]]\n* [[Buster Jones]]\n* [[Frank Nelson (actor)|Frank Nelson]]\n* [[Marilyn Schreffler]]\n* [[Lurene Tuttle]]\n* [[Paul Winchell]]\n\n==Home media==\nIn the 1980s, two [[VHS|videocassette]] editions of ''The Flintstone Comedy Show'' were released:\n\n* ''The Flintstone Comedy Show: 25th Silver Anniversary Special'', a 60-minute cassette containing six episodes (\"Mountain Frustration\", \"Potion Problem\", \"Camp-Out Mouse\", \"Clownfoot\", \"The Ghost Sitters\", \"Sands of the Saharastone\"), was released by [[Worldvision Enterprises|Worldvision Home Video]] in 1985.\n* ''The Flintstone Comedy Show 2: Curtain Call'', a 60-minute cassette containing six episodes (\"Gold Fever\", \"Night on the Town\", \"Monster Madness\", \"Arcade Antics\", \"Follow That Dogosaurus\", \"Be Patient, Fred\"), was released by Worldvision Home Video in 1986.\n\nCurrently{{when|date=August 2019}}, ''The Flintstone Comedy Show'' is streaming on the [[Boomerang_(TV_network)#Mobile_app/subscription_service|Boomerang]] streaming service as ''Flintstone Frolics''.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0923172}}\n* {{tv.com show|the-flintstone-comedy-show|The Flintstone Comedy Show}}\n* [https://www.bcdb.com/cartoons/Hanna-Barbera_Studios/D-F/The_Flintstone_Comedy_Show_1980_/ ''The Flintstone Comedy Show''] at [[The Big Cartoon DataBase]]\n\n{{The Flintstones}}\n{{Li'l Abner}}\n{{Children's programming on NBC in the 1980s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Flintstone Comedy Show (1980), The}}\n[[Category:The Flintstones spin-offs]]\n[[Category:1980 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:1981 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:1980s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:American animated television spin-offs]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated mystery television series]]\n[[Category:Crossover animated television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:NBC original programming]]\n[[Category:American police comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by Hanna-Barbera]]\n[[Category:Television series set in prehistory]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eThe Frankenstones", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Flintstone_Comedy_Show"}
{"title_page": "Heosphora desertella", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n| image = \n| taxon = Heosphora desertella\n| authority = [[George Hampson|Hampson]], 1918\n| synonyms = *''Saluria desertella'' <small>Hampson, 1918</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Heosphora desertella''''' is a species of [[moth]] in the family [[Pyralidae]]. The species was first described by [[George Hampson]] in 1918.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/lepindex/detail/?taxonno=8212&page_no=1&page_size=30|title=LepIndex \u2013 desertella|website=www.nhm.ac.uk|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biolib.cz/en/taxon/id1101611/|title=BioLib: Biological library|last=ondrej.zicha(at)gmail.com|first=Ondrej Zicha;|website=www.biolib.cz|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bie.ala.org.au/species/urn:lsid:biodiversity.org.au:afd.taxon:dfd17646-7fbb-428f-b52e-458f86cb9b13|title=Species: Heosphora desertella|last=Australia|first=Atlas of Living|website=bie.ala.org.au|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Pyralidae]]\n\n\n{{Pyralidae-stub}}\n[[Category:Moths of Australia]]\n[[Category:Moths described in 1918]]\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n| image = \n| taxon = Heosphora desertella\n| authority = [[George Hampson|Hampson]], 1918\n| synonyms = *''Saluria desertella'' <small>Hampson, 1918</small>\n}}\n\n'''''Heosphora desertella''''' is a species of [[moth]] in the family [[Pyralidae]]. The species was first described by [[George Hampson]] in 1918.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhm.ac.uk/our-science/data/lepindex/detail/?taxonno=8212&page_no=1&page_size=30|title=LepIndex - desertella|website=www.nhm.ac.uk|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.biolib.cz/en/taxon/id1101611/|title=BioLib: Biological library|last=ondrej.zicha(at)gmail.com|first=Ondrej Zicha;|website=www.biolib.cz|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bie.ala.org.au/species/urn:lsid:biodiver