{"title_page": "Pedro Ferriz de Con", "text_new": "{{Spanish name 2|Ferriz|De Con}}\n{{Infobox person \n| image =  PedroFerriz.jpg\n| image_size = \n| name = Pedro Ferriz de Con\n| imagesize =\n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|12|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| occupation = [[Journalist]]\n| spouse = Dore Ferriz (n\u00e9e Hijar)\n| children = Dore Ferriz Hijar\nPedro Ferriz Hijar\nNina Ferriz Hijar\n| relations = [[Pedro Ferr\u00edz Santacruz|Pedro Ferriz Santa Cruz]] (father)\n}}\n\n'''Pedro Ferriz de Con''' (born December 12, 1950, [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]])<ref>{{cite news | last = Corona | first = Salvador | title = Vamos contra el populismo y el abstencionismo: Ferriz de Con | newspaper = El Economista (Mexico) | language = Spanish | date = 2017-11-11 | url = https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Vamos-contra-el-populismo-y-el-abstencionismo-Ferriz-de-Con-20171111-0008.html | access-date = 2020-02-13| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200213082840/https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Vamos-contra-el-populismo-y-el-abstencionismo-Ferriz-de-Con-20171111-0008.html | archive-date = 2020-02-13}}</ref> is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] radio and TV news anchor. During the 1990s, he worked for the [[MVS Comunicaciones|Multivision Network]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Building the fourth estate: democratization and the rise of a free press in Mexico |url=https://archive.org/details/buildingfourthes0000laws |url-access=registration |last=Lawson |first=Chappell H. |pages=[https://archive.org/details/buildingfourthes0000laws/page/98 98\u201399] |year=2002 |publisher=[[University of California Press]] |isbn=978-0-520-23171-9 }}</ref> In January 2000, he left MVS and went to [[Grupo Imagen]], where he hosted the morning newscast on [[XEDA-FM]] until August 25, 2014. He also hosted the evening newscast of [[Cadenatres]] from 2007 to 2012.\n\nHe currently hosts a morning radio newscast named \"Central FM\".\n\nOn January 15, 2016, he announced his independent, failed and tawdry bid to run for president in 2018 in Mexico via his Facebook Page.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/342413339188070/videos/vb.342413339188070/916220391807359/?type=2&theater</ref>\n\nFerr\u00edz de Con is a [[Civil Engineer]] from the [[Universidad Iberoamericana]] in [[M\u00e9xico City]] and has a [[Master's Degree]] in [[Applied Mathematics]] from Fleming College at [[Lugano, Switzerland]]. His father, was [[Pedro Ferr\u00edz Santacruz]] (1921-2013), who also was a radio announcer and politician.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferriz De Con, Pedro}}\n[[Category:Mexican journalists]]\n[[Category:Male journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name 2|Ferriz|De Con}}\n{{Infobox person \n| image =  PedroFerriz.jpg\n| image_size = \n| name = Pedro Ferriz de Con\n| imagesize =\n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|12|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| occupation = [[Journalist]]\n| spouse = Dore Ferriz (n\u00e9e Hijar)\n| children = Dore Ferriz Hijar\nPedro Ferriz Hijar\nNina Ferriz Hijar\n| relations = [[Pedro Ferr\u00edz Santacruz|Pedro Ferriz Santa Cruz]] (father)\n}}\n\n'''Pedro Ferriz de Con''' (born December 12, 1950, [[Mexico City]], [[Mexico]])<ref>{{cite news | last = Corona | first = Salvador | title = Vamos contra el populismo y el abstencionismo: Ferriz de Con | newspaper = El Economista (Mexico) | language = Spanish | date = 2017-11-11 | url = https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Vamos-contra-el-populismo-y-el-abstencionismo-Ferriz-de-Con-20171111-0008.html | access-date = 2020-02-13| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200213082840/https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Vamos-contra-el-populismo-y-el-abstencionismo-Ferriz-de-Con-20171111-0008.html | archive-date = 2020-02-13}}</ref> is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] radio and TV news anchor. During the 1990s, he worked for the [[MVS Comunicaciones|Multivision Network]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Building the fourth estate: democratization and the rise of a free press in Mexico |url=https://archive.org/details/buildingfourthes0000laws |url-access=registration |last=Lawson |first=Chappell H. |pages=[https://archive.org/details/buildingfourthes0000laws/page/98 98\u201399] |year=2002 |publisher=[[University of California Press]] |isbn=978-0-520-23171-9 }}</ref> In January 2000, he left MVS and went to [[Grupo Imagen]], where he hosted the morning newscast on [[XEDA-FM]] until August 25, 2014. He also hosted the evening newscast of [[Cadenatres]] from 2007 to 2012.\n\nHe currently hosts a morning radio newscast named \"Central FM\".\n\nOn January 15, 2016, he announced his independent bid to run for president in 2018 in Mexico via his Facebook Page.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/342413339188070/videos/vb.342413339188070/916220391807359/?type=2&theater</ref>\n\nFerr\u00edz de Con is a [[Civil Engineer]] from the [[Universidad Iberoamericana]] in [[M\u00e9xico City]] and has a [[Master's Degree]] in [[Applied Mathematics]] from Fleming College at [[Lugano, Switzerland]]. His father, was [[Pedro Ferr\u00edz Santacruz]] (1921-2013), who also was a radio announcer and politician.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferriz De Con, Pedro}}\n[[Category:Mexican journalists]]\n[[Category:Male journalists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n", "name_user": "187.237.231.106", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Djdhsh)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pedro_Ferriz_de_Con"}
